Data Science as a "Second Calling"
========================================================

## Data science draws on many disciplines
- Much of its theoretical basis comes from statistics
- Its way of proceeding draws heavily on scientific research
- Strongly influenced by technology and software engineering methodologies


Data Science as a "Second Calling"
========================================================

## Data science is often a "second calling"
- Many data scientists started out as programmers, statisticians, business
intelligence analysts or scientists
- Already mastered a number of the skills needed for data science - add
some more to their repertoire to turn into effective data scientists


Skills of a Data Scientist
========================================================

*So, what skills does a data scientist need to have?*

Data science as such is a relatively new field and, honestly, there isn't
a unanimous view of what a curriculum on this subject should look like.
What is clear, however, is that **you need to learn/know quite a lot of stuff.**

